<biogHist>
<abstract>Eva Bacon settled in Australia after Hitler's invasion of Austria in 1938. Jim McIlroy, in his tribute to Eva in the <span style="font-style:italic">Green Left Weekly</span>, writes that "she continued her life-long struggle for peace, socialism and the emancipation of women in her new homeland through her activism in the Communist Party of Australia and a variety of of other progressive organisations."

Eva was a member of the Communist Party of Australia, the Union of Australian Women and the Women's Electoral Lobby. She was also a founding member of the International Womens' Day Committee. She was married to her husband Ted for almost 50 years and they had one daughter, Barbara.  

(Source: <span style="font-style:italic">http://www.greenleft.org.au/back/1994/155/155p5d.htm</span> accessed 18/11/2002)</abstract>

</biogHist>
